answers.answer: Headaches are not uncommon during pregnancy. You can take tylenol to ease the pain :)

Omg yes!!!! It was so bad I just knew I had preeclampsia, but whenever I take my bp it's good. So make sure your bp and bs are good. I never ever get headaches,  but this last week was awful. Fortunately Tylenol does help, but it *****:( Also, try taking more naps and make sure you're getting enough water. Hopefully this is just a temporary phase for us. Good luck!

Glad to know i'm not the only one! Its so horrible and it came all of a sudden. Fades for an hour or so then comes right back. I was prescribed tylenol with codeine, but im nervous to take it. Hopefully this will all clear up for the both of us asap! Im so tired of it
My midwife told me to call if I get a headache that won't go away. Could be a sign of preeclampsia. Probably not but good to be safe. I would call Dr if it won't go away and just check in.
If your not a big caffeine dribker
If your not a big caffeine drinker a can of caffeinated soda should ease a head ache.
